  "_comment": "Cross-platform contract for builder-paywall decoding + text/variable semantics. The TS authoring schema is STRICT (unknown node types are rejected: acceptLenient entries FAIL it). Platform decoders (Swift Codable, Kotlin kotlinx-serialization) are lenient by design: unknown node types decode to an unknown node retaining id+fallback and render the fallback (or nothing); an override entry with an unknown `when.kind` is skipped individually (that one entry ignored, config otherwise decodes normally) — also acceptLenient, per the unknown-condition-kind leniency rule (spec D2/D3). reject entries must fail EVERYWHERE (schema AND platform decoders → null), including a structural key (e.g. `type`) inside override props on an otherwise-KNOWN when.kind — malformed props in a known kind is a whole-config failure, not a skippable entry. Overrides APPLICATION semantics (base props, then matching overrides in array order, later wins, shallow per-field) are pinned by per-platform unit tests sharing D-Task 1's TS case table (schema.test.ts / validate.test.ts `applyOverrides` cases) — NOT by fixture sections here, since applying overrides needs live selected/introEligible state the static fixture format doesn't carry. Generated from the real TS implementations; frozen — regenerate only by re-running the generator against packages/shared/src/paywall.",
